<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#000033">I take offense to vulgar language. Is it filtered out?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>That's a great question! Vulgar language is censored out by the Message Board. The option is available for message board administrators to either allow all language in all posts or to filter out posts with a language filter. This filter is customizable by the message board administrator, so if you feel that a word is vulgar to you and the word is not currently being filtered, contact the message board administrator and ask them to filter the word(s).<p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#000033">Can I search the message board?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>The Message Board has a search feature built in. You are able to search not only single forums but also all forums, including all subjects and message posts.
	<p>
	<div align="center">
		<img src="faq/search.gif" border="1" width="515" height="215">
	</div>
		<br>
		<ul>
		<li><b>1.</b> "Search All Forums" - Select this to search all forums on the Message Board.<br>
		<li><b>2.</b> "Search In Subject Headers" - Select this to search all subjects in either one board or all boards.<br>
		<li><b>3.</b> "Search In Posts" - [Default Setting] Select this to search all posts in either one board or all boards.<br>
		<li><b>4.</b> "Select Forum" - Select which forum you'd like to search. [Not used when "Search All Forums" is selected]<br>
		<li><b>5.</b> "For The Term" - Type your search terms here.
		</ul>
		<p>
		&nbsp;Click <a href=default.asp?dest=search&siteid=1000>here</a> to try a search!
	<p>
	</td>
</tr>
